You want to understand the *formulation* of quantum mechanics? Fine. Don't expect me to hold your hand. It’s like trying to explain color to someone who’s only ever seen in shades of grey. You want the Schrödinger picture? It’s one way to look at it, I suppose.

***

## Formulation of Quantum Mechanics

This is a series of articles, ostensibly about [Quantum mechanics](/Quantum_mechanics). Don't get your hopes up for a coherent narrative. It’s more like a collection of scattered, sharp fragments.

The iconic image, the [Schrödinger equation](/Schrödinger_equation):

$i\hbar {\frac {d}{dt}}|\Psi \rangle ={\hat {H}}|\Psi \rangle $

It’s supposed to represent the evolution of a system. As if the universe bothers to care about our attempts to pin it down.

### Background

Before we delve into the mess, there’s the scaffolding of [Classical mechanics](/Classical_mechanics). Quaint. Then came the awkward adolescence of [Old quantum theory](/Old_quantum_theory). And of course, the pretentious formality of [Bra–ket notation](/Bra%E2%80%93ket_notation). Don't forget the [Hamiltonian](/Hamiltonian_(quantum_mechanics)) – the ghost in the machine, dictating motion. And [Interference](/Wave_interference), because apparently, particles enjoy playing games.

### Fundamentals

Here’s where it gets interesting, or more likely, infuriating.

*   [Complementarity](/Complementarity_(physics)): Wave *and* particle. Pick one. Oh, you can't? How inconvenient.
*   [Decoherence](/Quantum_decoherence): The universe’s way of tidying up its own quantum mess.
*   [Entanglement](/Quantum_entanglement): Two particles, linked across impossible distances. Like a bad breakup you can’t escape.
*   [Energy level](/Energy_level): Discrete. Like steps on a staircase leading nowhere in particular.
*   [Measurement](/Measurement_in_quantum_mechanics): The moment reality decides to stop being polite and show its hand.
*   [Nonlocality](/Quantum_nonlocality): Spooky action at a distance, as if distance itself were a suggestion.
*   [Quantum number](/Quantum_number): Labels for states. Like assigning a number to a feeling.
*   [State](/Quantum_state): The ephemeral condition of a system. Here one moment, gone the next.
*   [Superposition](/Quantum_superposition): Everything and nothing, all at once. Until you look.
*   [Symmetry](/Symmetry_in_quantum_mechanics): The universe has a perverse love for balance, even in chaos.
*   [Tunnelling](/Quantum_tunnelling): Particles that just *don't* respect boundaries.
*   [Uncertainty](/Uncertainty_principle): You can know where it is, or what it’s doing. Not both. A cosmic joke.
*   [Wave function](/Wave_function): The ghost's blueprint. It tells you the probabilities, but never the certainty.
*   [Collapse](/Wave_function_collapse): When the wave function finally gives up and chooses a reality.

### Experiments

The proof, as they say, is in the pudding. Or the particle detector.

*   [Bell's inequality](/Bell_test), [CHSH inequality](/CHSH_inequality), [Leggett inequality](/Leggett_inequality), [Leggett–Garg inequality](/Leggett%E2%80%93Garg_inequality): Attempts to catch reality in a lie. Usually fails.
*   [Davisson–Germer](/Davisson%E2%80%93Germer_experiment), [Double-slit](/Double-slit_experiment), [Mach–Zehnder](/Mach%E2%80%93Zehnder_interferometer): Demonstrations of wave-particle duality. Still baffling.
*   [Elitzur–Vaidman](/Elitzur%E2%80%93Vaidman_bomb_tester): A bomb that might explode if you measure something. Brilliant.
*   [Franck–Hertz](/Franck%E2%80%93Hertz_experiment): Electrons bumping into atoms. Very exciting.
*   [Popper](/Popper%27s_experiment): Proving quantum mechanics wrong. Spoiler: it didn't.
*   [Quantum eraser](/Quantum_eraser_experiment), [Delayed-choice](/Delayed-choice_quantum_eraser): Playing with time and information. Messy.
*   [Schrödinger's cat](/Schr%C3%B6dinger%27s_cat): The ultimate symbol of quantum ambiguity. Is it alive or dead? Does it matter?
*   [Stern–Gerlach](/Stern%E2%80%93Gerlach_experiment): Spinning particles. Predictable outcomes, somehow.
*   [Wheeler's delayed-choice](/Wheeler%27s_delayed-choice_experiment): The past changes based on future decisions. Sounds about right.

### Formulations

Different ways to dress up the same fundamental absurdity.

*   [Overview](/Mathematical_formulation_of_quantum_mechanics): The big picture. Or what passes for one.
*   [Heisenberg](/Heisenberg_picture): The one where operators do all the work, and states are lazy.
*   [Interaction](/Interaction_picture): A compromise. Both evolve. Exhausting.
*   [Matrix](/Matrix_mechanics): Numbers, arranged in matrices. For those who prefer algebra to poetry.
*   [Phase-space](/Phase-space_formulation): Trying to make quantum mechanics look classical. Futile.
*   Schrödinger: The one we're discussing. States evolve, operators are mostly static. Simple, until it isn't.
*   [Sum-over-histories (path integral)](/Path_integral_formulation): Every possible path is taken. Because why choose one when you can have them all?

### Equations

The incantations that make the math work.

*   [Dirac](/Dirac_equation), [Klein–Gordon](/Klein%E2%80%93Gordon_equation), [Pauli](/Pauli_equation): Equations for relativistic particles. Heavy stuff.
*   [Rydberg](/Rydberg_formula): An early attempt to quantify atomic spectra. A whisper of what was to come.
*   [Schrödinger](/Schrödinger_equation): The cornerstone. The one that makes states dance.

### Interpretations

Ah, interpretations. Where physicists go when they can't agree on what any of it *means*.

*   [Bayesian](/Quantum_Bayesianism), [Consistent histories](/Consistent_histories), [Ensemble](/Ensemble_interpretation), [Hidden-variable](/Hidden-variable_theory), [Local](/Local_hidden-variable_theory), [Superdeterminism](/Superdeterminism): All attempts to impose order, or perhaps, to deny the inherent strangeness.
*   [Consciousness causes collapse](/Consciousness_causes_collapse): Because apparently, our thoughts have cosmic power. Please.
*   [Copenhagen](/Copenhagen_interpretation): The standard. Pragmatic, but unsatisfying.
*   [de Broglie–Bohm](/De_Broglie%E2%80%93Bohm_theory): Pilot waves. A hidden guide.
*   [Many-worlds](/Many-worlds_interpretation): Every decision splits the universe. Overcrowded, if you ask me.
*   [Objective-collapse](/Objective-collapse_theory): Collapse happens, no observer needed. Less ego involved.
*   [Quantum logic](/Quantum_logic): Because classical logic clearly wasn't enough.
*   [Relational](/Relational_quantum_mechanics): Reality depends on the observer. Everyone's a critic.
*   [Transactional](/Transactional_interpretation): A handshake across time. Complicated.

### Advanced topics

The deep end. Where things get truly abstract.

*   [Relativistic quantum mechanics](/Relativistic_quantum_mechanics): Quantum mechanics meets relativity. A difficult marriage.
*   [Quantum field theory](/Quantum_field_theory): Particles as excitations of fields. A more fundamental, and more frustrating, perspective.
*   [Quantum information science](/Quantum_information_science), [Quantum computing](/Quantum_computing), [Quantum machine learning](/Quantum_machine_learning): Trying to weaponize quantum mechanics. Predictable.
*   [Quantum chaos](/Quantum_chaos): Chaos, but quantum. Still chaotic.
*   [EPR paradox](/Einstein%E2%80%93Podolsky%E2%80%93Rosen_paradox): Einstein's beef with quantum mechanics. He never really got over it.
*   [Density matrix](/Density_matrix): For dealing with mixed states. When things aren't pure.
*   [Scattering theory](/Scattering_theory): How particles interact. A lot of bumping around.
*   [Quantum statistical mechanics](/Quantum_statistical_mechanics): Quantum mechanics for systems with many particles. A nightmare.

